snippet.textDisplay: I'm not surprised that ChromeOS has overtaken Mac in user base. If you think about it, there's a huge upsurge in people needing student computers. I've heard so often people saying "I literally can't imagine paying more than $200 for a top dollar computer" when I was trying to help sell some budget rigs around $500 ("Fortnite" machines). Basically, people are starting to view PCs as a must have, but also can't imagine one that is what us 'elite types' would actually call a competent PC. They just need to email and doc. They can do that for $100-200, so even $500 seems astonishing. Not to mention the $700-1200 many of us pay for mid to lower-high end performance.
snippet.textOriginal: I'm not surprised that ChromeOS has overtaken Mac in user base. If you think about it, there's a huge upsurge in people needing student computers.
